title: Jesse Ventura - Ballotpedia
snippet: Please contact us with any updates. ... Jesse Ventura was the Governor of Minnesota. Ventura assumed office on January 8, 1999. Ventura left office on January 6, 2003. Ventura (Green Party of Alaska, Unaffiliated) ran for election for President of the United States.

title: Jesse Ventura: A Profile | MPR Archive Portal
snippet: He was the first and only candidate of the Reform Party to win a major government position. In his role as governor, he was known for both his independence and combativeness with political parties and the press.
